<br>
Cleric:<br>
Blessing of Aegolism (presumably MGBed and screw the PoG/Marzin's stuff... it is so minimal as to be a waste of time.  Your raid will be that much less sharp for screwing around over ~50HP.)<br>
Elixers (I save a slot, you might not need to.)<br>
<br>
Shaman:<br>
Focus (MGBed)<br>
Primal Essence (if you need the stats like stamina, I do.)<br>
Primal Avatar (for attack and presuming no Primal/PE, though you need a slot for that anyways.  If it is not available perhaps Bih' Li for attack.)<br>
Talisman of the Brute (assuming you need stamina, Bristlebane knows I do.)<br>
Talismans of X (saves are nice in many encounters, of course they are ass in most and now that ToE and Shadoo no longer stack... well damn.)<br>
<br>
Druid:<br>
Seasons if applicable, nothing if not.<br>
<br>
Mage: <br>
Damage Shield of some sort and a mod rod so you can scare the healers.  (I also like to ask them for strange summoned items to make them feel loved.  Come on now, you want to do things without CoH all the time?  I recommend fireworks or spin the bottle.)<br>
<br>
Ranger/Paladin:<br>
CoP (unless stacking issues, I don't get any though and attack is my god)<br>
SoN (for attack, tanks take Brell's)<br>
CoE (/shrug Some folks seem to like it... I always get stacking bs.)<br>
<br>
Enchanter:<br>
VoG (for attack again, some tanks like SoS for the AC. Haha!)<br>
Rune if you feel annoying...<br>
<br>
Beastlord:<br>
Savagery (got Beastlord? Actually, I don't so I don't know stacking issues even.  It looks good enough to give the fools a reason to exist though.)<br>
<br>
Bard: (save slots for:)<br>
Dance of the Blade (epic proc, group only and gives nice attack.  Of course you are in the tank group so =p)<br>
Warsong of whatsisname (haste cap breaker and such, much love)<br>
Resists/regen Good if you have room and/or need them for the fight.<br>
<br>
Items: Get what you can and see how it stacks.  Ring 10 is big for a warrior though I imagine.  AoB and such are nice for everyone.  I am not into the whole &quot;how to stack damage shields&quot; business but save slots as needed for those of course.  Damage shields certainly add up.  Visit Lucy perhaps to see how your clickers work with what you want.<br>
<br>
New Spells:<br>
Aw heck, I am going to need to change all my gear now anyways.  I finally had it to max stamina in raid buffs and now I'll need to dump things for pure HP.  Oh well, who am I to argue?<br>
